## F1 Edu-Racer – Tech Stack Specification

---

### 1. **Frontend**

#### **Core Game Framework**
- **[Phaser.js v3.60+](mdc:https:/phaser.io/phaser3)**
  - Game scenes, physics, camera, input, sprite rendering.
  - Modular structure, WebGL & Canvas support.
  - Install via npm:
    ```bash
    npm install phaser
    ```

#### **Rendering & Web Environment**
- **HTML5 + Canvas API** (built into Phaser)
- **JavaScript (ES6+)** – core game logic and utilities
- **Vite** – lightweight dev server and bundler
  - Fast, hot-reloading, ideal for game dev
  - [https://vitejs.dev/](mdc:https:/vitejs.dev)
  - Install:
    ```bash
    npm create vite@latest
    ```

#### **UI and Menus**
- **Phaser GUI Plugin** *(or custom Phaser scenes)*
  - Menu overlays, HUD elements, tooltips.
- Optional: [RexUI](mdc:https:/rexrainbow.github.io/phaser3-rex-notes/docs/site/ui-overview)
  - Powerful UI toolkit for Phaser.

---

### 2. **Game Assets Tools**

| Type | Tool | Purpose |
|------|------|---------|
| **Sprites & Icons** | [GIMP](mdc:https:/www.gimp.org) / [Figma](mdc:https:/www.figma.com) / [Photoshop](mdc:https:/www.adobe.com/in/products/photoshop.html) | Create cars, tracks, HUD elements |
| **Spritesheet Packing** | [TexturePacker](mdc:https:/www.codeandweb.com/texturepacker) | Bundle animations |
| **Map Design** | [Tiled Map Editor](mdc:https:/www.mapeditor.org) | Design top-down tracks in 2D |
| **Audio FX** | [Bfxr](mdc:https:/bfxr.net) / [Audacity](mdc:https:/www.audacityteam.org) | Create engine, collision, UI sounds |

---

### 3. **State Management & Storage**

- **LocalStorage API** – built into browsers  
  - Store settings, progress, achievements  
  - No external setup required  
  - [MDN Docs](mdc:https:/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Window/localStorage)

---

### 4. **APIs for Ghost Mode (Phase 3)**

- **[Ergast API](mdc:https:/ergast.com/mrd)**
  - Source for F1 lap times, sector data, driver info
  - Free and community-maintained
  - Format: JSON/XML

  Example usage:
  ```bash
  https://ergast.com/api/f1/2023/monaco/qualifying.json
  ```

- **[Axios](mdc:https:/axios-http.com)**
  - Promise-based HTTP client
  - Install:
    ```bash
    npm install axios
    ```

---

### 5. **Performance & Optimization**

- **[Stats.js](mdc:https:/github.com/mrdoob/stats.js)**
  - Lightweight FPS and performance monitor
- **[TinyPNG](mdc:https:/tinypng.com)** – Compress sprites
- **[SVGO](mdc:https:/github.com/svg/svgo)** – Optimize SVG assets

---

### 6. **Testing & Debugging**

- **Chrome DevTools** – JS profiling, FPS, memory
- **[Jest](mdc:https:/jestjs.io)** – Optional for testing core logic/utils
  ```bash
  npm install --save-dev jest
  ```

---

### 7. **Deployment Tools**

- **[Netlify](mdc:https:/www.netlify.com)** or **[Vercel](mdc:https:/vercel.com)**
  - Easy drag-and-drop or GitHub CI/CD hosting
  - Free tier supports global CDN
- **[GitHub Pages](mdc:https:/pages.github.com)** – Alternate for lightweight hosting

---

### 8. **Version Control & Team Collaboration**

- **Git** + **GitHub**
  - Branching, Pull Requests, Issues, Project Boards
- Optional: **Notion** or **Trello** for roadmap and asset tracking

---

### 9. **Optional Stretch Tools**

| Feature | Tool | Use |
|--------|------|-----|
| Leaderboards / Cloud Saves | [Supabase](mdc:https:/supabase.com) or [Firebase](mdc:https:/firebase.google.com) | Simple backend-as-a-service |
| Multiplayer (future) | [Colyseus](mdc:https:/www.colyseus.io) | Node.js-based real-time multiplayer server |
| Analytics | [PostHog](mdc:https:/posthog.com) or Google Analytics | Track usage, session events |

